        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1151410623" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2588985060043028812">I swithered between 4 and 5 stars for this review. I found it a great read, an old-fashioned rattling good yarn. The characters are all engaging and the story moves along at a cracking pace. Now and again I drew my breath in sharply at some of the derogatory names used and attitudes shown towards people of races different to those whom Richard Hannay describes admiringly as &quot;white men&quot;. <br/><br/>Then I considered, not that it justifies those attitudes, that he was writing a century ago. Also, the hero ha</span>
  <span id="freeText2588985060043028812" style="display:none">I swithered between 4 and 5 stars for this review. I found it a great read, an old-fashioned rattling good yarn. The characters are all engaging and the story moves along at a cracking pace. Now and again I drew my breath in sharply at some of the derogatory names used and attitudes shown towards people of races different to those whom Richard Hannay describes admiringly as "white men". <br /><br />Then I considered, not that it justifies those attitudes, that he was writing a century ago. Also, the hero has a different attitude when he meets real people who belong to races or nationalities different to his own. For example, he's kind to the widowed German woman who shelters him when he's in Germany, at that time behind enemy lines.<br /><br />Ultimately I gave it 5 stars because it's a damn good read. I'm surprised no one's ever filmed it. It's very Indiana Jones. <br /><br /><br /><br /> </span>
